FBIS4-53677 "dreas099_a_94013" FBIS-EAS-94-099 Daily Report 22 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Patrol Boats Watch Ship for Illegal Asians Patrol Boats Watch Ship for Illegal Asians OW2205100994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0914 GMT 22 May 94 OW2205100994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, May 22 KYODO -- A Honduras-flagged freighter with some 60 non-Japanese Asians on board is approaching southern Japan, TBS TV reported Sunday [22 May]. Five patrol boats are keeping watch on the 500-ton vessel, identified as the Montana, which was spotted in waters some 35 kilometers off Tanegashima Island, Kagoshima Prefecture, Tokyo Broadcasting System said. The vessel is sailing slowly west-northwest, it said. Maritime Safety Agency officials suspect the passengers may be attempting to enter Japan illegally, TBS said. On Wednesday, a group of 138 Chinese were apprehended while hiding in a warehouse at Hakata port in Fukuoka. They were arrested for allegedly entering the country illegally.
